election_record.label: Virginia 1804 Electoral College

overview.note: There was no statewide slate of electors for Charles Cotesworth Pickney. Many counties listed their own slate of electors and only a handful of candidates received votes from multiple counties. Many of the candidates on the individual slates are unknown and many of the slates do not specifically state that they are Federalist tickets or specifically for Pinckney.

sub_unit.name: Augusta
sub_unit.note: Bernard Markham received 1 vote as Ronard Markham, 1 vote as Bernard Barkham and 1 vote as Barnard Markham.
Burdett Ashton received 10 votes as Burdett Ashson.
Carter Braxton received 3 votes as Carter Baxton.
Charles Dabney received 1 vote with the wrong county listed.
George K. Taylor received 4 votes as George R. Taylor, 2 votes as George H. Taylor and 2 votes as George Taylor.
Joel Leftwich received 9 votes with the wrong county listed and 1 vote as Joel Leftword.
John Blackwell received 1 vote as John Blagwell.
Robert Grattin received 1 vote as Jobert Grattin.
Sterling Edwards received 1 vote as Sterling Edward and 1 vote as Stuart Edwards.
Thomas Wilson received 1 vote as Thomas Winson.
William H. Cabell received 22 votes as William Cabell on the opposition ticket and 6 votes as William Cable on the opposition ticket.
Archibald Magill received 4 votes as Richard Magill.

sub_unit.name: Bedford
sub_unit.note: Levin Powell received 1 vote as Lewis Dowell.

sub_unit.name: Brooke
sub_unit.note: William Dudley received 1 vote as W. Dudley.
John Preston received 1 vote as J. Preston.
Archibald Stuart received 1 vote with the wrong county listed.

sub_unit.name: Campbell
sub_unit.note: Three of the votes for James Allen listed the wrong county.

sub_unit.name: Chesterfield
sub_unit.note: National Intelligencer and The Universal Gazette list 130 votes for the Jefferson Ticket.
William MacKinley received 1 vote as William Kinley.
John Taliaferio received 3 votes as J. Taliaferro.
Richard Field received 1 vote as Thomas Field.

sub_unit.name: Culpeper
sub_unit.note: All 24 members of the Republican Ticket received 4 votes with no counties listed and 10 votes with the incorrect counties listed.
George Wythe received 1 vote as George With.
James MacFarlane received 1 vote as James MacFarland.

sub_unit.name: Fairfax
sub_unit.note: Eighteen unknown Federalist electors received 16 votes each on a ticket headed by John Nevison.
Fifteen unknown Federalist electors received 2 votes each on a ticket headed by Charles Catlet.
Twenty-eight unknown Federalist electors received 1 vote each on a ticket headed by Jacob McConnetigh.

sub_unit.name: Gloucester
sub_unit.note: Twenty-four unknown electors received 1 vote each on a ticket headed by William Vaughun.

sub_unit.name: Greenbrier
sub_unit.note: James Allen received 2 votes as part of the Federalist ticket.
William H. Cabell received 2 votes as part of the Federalist ticket.

sub_unit.name: Kanawha
sub_unit.note: No results have been located from Kanawha County.

sub_unit.name: King George
sub_unit.note: George Wythe received 9 votes as George White.

sub_unit.name: Lancaster
sub_unit.note: John D. Watkins received 1 vote as John Watkins.
William H. Cabell received 5 votes as William Cabell on the opposition ticket.

sub_unit.name: Mecklenburg
sub_unit.note: Among the candidates receiving one vote there was a vote for "Democratical Republican of Frederick".

sub_unit.name: Monongalia
sub_unit.note: There were twenty-six different Federalist Tickets, all of which received 1 vote.

sub_unit.name: null
sub_unit.note: The results from Norfolk County were reported separately from Norfolk Borough, even though Norfolk Borough was in the county.

sub_unit.name: Pendleton
sub_unit.note: William H. Cabell received 10 votes as part of the Federalist ticket.

sub_unit.name: Randolph
sub_unit.note: There were various Federalist tickets in Randolph County, confusing even the officials. Thirteen sets of electors were listed and several had some Republican names. The official listed most of the tickets as thus: "and as for the rest of the Federal tickets . . . they appear to us to be rather fictitious."

sub_unit.name: Rockingham
sub_unit.note: William MacKinley received 1 vote as James MacKinley.
Edward Pegram received 1 vote as Edward Pagin.
William Dudley received 1 vote as John Dudley.
John Goodrich received 1 vote as George Goodrich and 1 vote as Edward Goodrich.
John Minor received 1 vote as John Maylor.
George Penn received 1 vote as George Patrick.
James MacFarland received 1 vote as James MacLane and 2 votes as James Farlane.
James Dailey received 2 votes as John Dudley and 1 vote as James Dudley.
Richard Evers Lee received 1 vote as R.E. Dee, 1 vote as Richard Evans Lee and 5 votes with the wrong county listed.
John Taliaferio, Jr. received 11 votes as William Talieferro, Jr..

sub_unit.name: Sussex
sub_unit.note: National Intelligencer and The Universal Gazette list 216 votes for the Jefferson Ticket.

sub_unit.name: Washington
sub_unit.note: James Allen received 1 vote with the wrong county listed by his name.

sub_unit.name: Williamsburg
sub_unit.note: At the time, Williamsburg was split between James City County and York County and was not yet an independent city. The votes in Williamsburg appear to have been reported independently of either county.

sub_unit.name: Wood
sub_unit.note: There were 24 unknown electors on a ticket headed by James Wilson that received 6 votes each.
There were 24 unknown electors on a ticket headed by William Wilson that received 2 votes each.

election_record.reference: Original Election Returns. Library of Virginia, Richmond.
National Intelligencer and Washington Advertiser (Washington, DC). November 16, 1804.
